    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="72"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 493.11/473.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of the
                            Treasury</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Treasury Department</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 30, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the communication dated the 22d
                    instant received from the Department of State, relative to payments made by the
                    Chinese Government on account of Chinese indemnity due for the calendar year
                    1913, I have the honor to enclose herewith, for delivery, as requested by your
                    Department, check No. 6900, of the Treasurer of the United States in the sum of
                    $543,007.63, payable to the Charge d’Affaires of China, which sum represents the
                    amount of such payments refundable to China as the portion of the indemnity for
                    the calendar year 1913 remitted under the joint resolution of May 25, 1908 (35
                    Stat., 577).</p>
                <p>Respectfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Skelton Williams</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
